After 23 letters/emails of rejections, 5 failed interviews, and words of discouragement in just this past year alone, I am proud to announce that I have accepted a summer internship as Software Dev Engineer for LPL Financial, which is the nation‚Äôs leading independent broker/dealer firm.

Although it may not be obvious, the last several years have been a struggle for me for many different reasons that most people do not know. And although, everything is not perfect, this is an unexpected positive in my life that I am very grateful for.

It is also bittersweet because I know a lot of my friends and peers who deserved an internship did not receive one or am, like myself, caught in a cycle of rejection. One thing I had to learn in this season was to stay humble, work hard when no one is watching, relax, build yourself, and remember that your life is on your timeline, not anyone else‚Äôs. Although it may seem like others are ahead or behind, they are just right on time and so are you.

Remember to help others if you have the ability and share what you learn. No one has ever done anything by themselves; We‚Äôve all received help or grace from someone in our tumultuous journey called Life.

Sincerely, -An Imperfect person trying to be less perfect
